      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHAROS FINALE (3) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fourth wasn't far away finishing 2.75 lengths from the winner (17.76). Solid record here at the distance winning three races. Has ability and is a key runner. SHADOW MAC (1) failed to feature last start after settling well back at Cannington, but prior to that won easily by 4 lengths at this track (17.43) beating Grandad Kevin in a LS6 on July 6. Should be about the money. CHAROS LEGEND (2) collided in the run last time but kept coming to hit the frame in a Grade 5/6 at this track (17.55). Leading player again. NEON LEON (6) is worth consideration after filling a hole at big odds last start.",
